00:12:00.940 --> 00:12:02.940
Yeah, well, I'm sure they could squeeze you in.

00:12:02.940 --> 00:12:03.940
I'll go give them a call.

00:12:03.940 --> 00:12:04.940
Thanks, Dad.

00:12:04.940 --> 00:12:06.940
But, um, you know, it's my bike,

00:12:06.940 --> 00:12:08.940
and I'm not a kid anymore.

00:12:08.940 --> 00:12:09.940
I'll call.

00:12:09.940 --> 00:12:10.940
Okay, Sport.

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:11.940
That's the way you want it.

00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:14.420
Study.

00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:21.380
Will they take me seriously?

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:23.380
I mean, what if they laugh at me?

00:12:23.380 --> 00:12:24.380
Wait a minute.

00:12:24.380 --> 00:12:25.380
What right do they have to laugh at me?

00:12:25.380 --> 00:12:26.380
I mean, I pay taxes.

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:28.380
Well, okay.

00:12:28.380 --> 00:12:30.380
Not me exactly, but people I'm related to do.

00:12:31.380 --> 00:12:32.380
Only one way to find out.

00:12:33.380 --> 00:12:37.490
Hello, operator.

00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:38.490
Get me the police.

00:12:39.490 --> 00:12:40.490
I've always wanted to say that.

00:12:45.300 --> 00:12:46.300
That's the way you wear it, Mom.

00:12:46.300 --> 00:12:48.300
Well, I just want you to look nice for the police, Azolla.

00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:49.300
Mom.

00:12:49.300 --> 00:13:02.550
Somebody call about a missing bike.

00:13:02.550 --> 00:13:03.550
That's me.

00:13:03.550 --> 00:13:04.550
Come.

00:13:04.550 --> 00:13:05.550
Hi, I'm Janet, darling.

00:13:05.550 --> 00:13:06.550
Come on in.

00:13:07.550 --> 00:13:09.550
Mom, I think I can handle this by myself.

00:13:09.550 --> 00:13:10.550
Okay, you go ahead.

00:13:10.550 --> 00:13:12.550
But I think I'll hang around, though.

00:13:12.550 --> 00:13:13.550
You close the darling?

00:13:13.550 --> 00:13:14.550
Uh-huh.

00:13:14.550 --> 00:13:15.550
I'm Officer Mustafa.

00:13:15.550 --> 00:13:17.550
This is Officer Baines.

00:13:17.550 --> 00:13:18.550
Hi.

00:13:18.550 --> 00:13:20.550
So you think you can catch whoever took my bike?

00:13:20.550 --> 00:13:21.550
Depends.

00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:22.550
You know who did it?

00:13:22.550 --> 00:13:23.550
Funny.

00:13:23.550 --> 00:13:25.550
Tell us about the bike.

00:13:25.550 --> 00:13:28.550
Well, I got it three years ago for my birthday,

00:13:28.550 --> 00:13:29.550
and it seemed like a big deal at the time,

00:13:29.550 --> 00:13:30.550
but what I really wanted was a car.

00:13:30.550 --> 00:13:32.550
But, you know, you need to learn this permit first.

00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:33.550
Uh-huh, we see.

00:13:33.550 --> 00:13:34.550
Back to the bike.

00:13:34.550 --> 00:13:35.550
Can you describe it?

00:13:35.550 --> 00:13:36.550
Okay.

00:13:36.550 --> 00:13:38.550
Um, it was a 26-inch girl's bike.

00:13:38.550 --> 00:13:40.550
And doesn't it have that cute license plate

00:13:40.550 --> 00:13:42.550
that says Clarissa on the back?

00:13:42.550 --> 00:13:43.550
Oh, my.

00:13:43.550 --> 00:13:45.550
I checked that off two years ago.

00:13:45.550 --> 00:13:48.550
Um, it was red with a wicker basket.

00:13:48.550 --> 00:13:49.550
Three-speed.

00:13:49.550 --> 00:13:52.550
This is why I joined the force.

00:13:52.550 --> 00:13:53.550
When did you last see the bike?

00:13:53.550 --> 00:13:54.550
Monday.

00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:55.550
Uh-huh, where?

00:13:55.550 --> 00:13:56.550
In the front yard.

00:13:56.550 --> 00:13:57.550
Locked?

00:13:57.550 --> 00:13:58.550
Not exactly.

00:13:58.550 --> 00:13:59.550
Unlocked for daylight?

00:13:59.550 --> 00:14:00.550
Unattended?

00:14:00.550 --> 00:14:01.550
Only for a minute.

00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:03.550
Can you imagine we were all in the house?

00:14:03.550 --> 00:14:04.550
Uh-huh.

00:14:04.550 --> 00:14:06.550
Are you getting all this down?

00:14:06.550 --> 00:14:07.550
Oh, yeah.

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:10.550
We'll let you know if something turns up.

00:14:10.550 --> 00:14:11.550
Is that it?

00:14:11.550 --> 00:14:13.550
Well, what else did you expect them to do, dear?

00:14:13.550 --> 00:14:16.550
I suppose we could fingerprint the lawn.

00:14:16.550 --> 00:14:18.550
We'll do everything that we can.

00:14:18.550 --> 00:14:20.550
So you think you can get my bike back?

00:14:20.550 --> 00:14:21.550
It's hard to say.

00:14:21.550 --> 00:14:22.550
We see a lot of cases like this.

00:14:22.550 --> 00:14:24.550
Try not to get your hopes up.

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:26.550
There isn't a very good recovery rate on bicycles.

00:14:26.550 --> 00:14:28.550
A bike gets stolen every three minutes.

00:14:28.550 --> 00:14:29.550
How often have I found?

00:14:29.550 --> 00:14:32.550
Let's just say we've been on this case for ten minutes.

00:14:32.550 --> 00:14:33.550
We haven't recovered a bike yet.

00:14:33.550 --> 00:14:35.550
So you figure it out.

00:14:35.550 --> 00:14:36.550
It was nice meeting you.

00:14:36.550 --> 00:14:37.550
Well, so long.

00:14:37.550 --> 00:14:38.550
Thanks for coming.

00:14:38.550 --> 00:14:40.550
Yeah, thanks.

00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:41.550
I think.

00:14:41.550 --> 00:14:43.550
Boy, they weren't much help.

00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.550
Well, we don't know that yet, dear.

00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:46.550
I don't know.

00:14:46.550 --> 00:14:47.550
They just didn't seem to care.

00:14:47.550 --> 00:14:49.550
Cops on TV at least pretend to be interested.

00:14:49.550 --> 00:14:51.550
Let's wait and see what turns up.

00:14:51.550 --> 00:14:54.950
Great.

00:14:54.950 --> 00:14:56.950
By the time they find my bike,

00:14:56.950 --> 00:14:58.950
the only wheels I'll need will be on my wheelchair.

00:14:58.950 --> 00:15:00.950
If I really want my bike back,

00:15:00.950 --> 00:15:02.950
I'm gonna have to go out and get it myself.

00:15:02.950 --> 00:15:04.950
Mom and Dad won't responsible.

00:15:04.950 --> 00:15:06.950
I'll give them responsible.

00:15:06.950 --> 00:15:08.950
So what if I don't have any wheels?

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:10.950
I can afford a little shoe leather finding my bike.

00:15:10.950 --> 00:15:12.950
Yeah, just like the old private eyes,

00:15:12.950 --> 00:15:14.950
I'll scour the neighborhood.

00:15:14.950 --> 00:15:16.950
I'll walk every inch of these mean streets.

00:15:16.950 --> 00:15:22.790
I can see it now.

00:15:22.790 --> 00:15:24.790
It was a cold, damp and dingy night.

00:15:24.790 --> 00:15:28.790
Like a sweat sock that had been worn to one gym class too many.

00:15:28.790 --> 00:15:29.790
But I didn't care.

00:15:29.790 --> 00:15:31.790
I had a job to do.

00:15:31.790 --> 00:15:33.790
It's easy losing a bike in this town.

00:15:33.790 --> 00:15:35.790
Hard parts getting it back.

00:15:35.790 --> 00:15:36.790
That's where I come in.

00:15:36.790 --> 00:15:37.790
Name's Darling.

00:15:37.790 --> 00:15:39.790
Clarissa Darling, P.I.

00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:41.790
I got a tip from Willie the Mole

00:15:41.790 --> 00:15:44.790
that something fishy was going on down at the docks.

00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:47.790
And I don't mean halibut.

00:15:47.790 --> 00:15:48.790
The docks.

00:15:48.790 --> 00:15:50.790
I hate the docks.

00:15:50.790 --> 00:15:52.790
Ordered the tuna salad.

00:15:52.790 --> 00:15:54.790
Extra mayo.

00:15:54.790 --> 00:15:57.790
Translation, the bike I was looking for

00:15:57.790 --> 00:15:59.790
had a one-way ticket to Shanghai

00:15:59.790 --> 00:16:01.790
unless somebody moved and fast.

00:16:01.790 --> 00:16:04.790
That somebody was me.

00:16:04.790 --> 00:16:11.740
Please, careful, careful.

00:16:11.740 --> 00:16:15.500
Happy to see me, Mr. Big.

00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:17.500
You're too late, my dear.

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:20.500
Your precious bike is as good as gone.

00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:22.500
Oh yeah?

00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:24.500
Tell that to my buddies in blue.

00:16:24.500 --> 00:16:26.500
Darling, we got your call.

00:16:26.500 --> 00:16:28.500
What's the big... Oh, Mr. Big.

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:30.500
We've got a nice place for you downtown.

00:16:30.500 --> 00:16:32.500
With bars on the window and everything.

00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:35.500
Game's set and matched to you, darling.

00:16:35.500 --> 00:16:38.500
But next time, I say...

00:16:38.500 --> 00:16:40.500
You could start serving now.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:42.500
Five to fifteen for bike theft.

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:44.500
All this fishing.

00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:46.500
He's starting to stink.

00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:55.300
Well, I still don't have a clue as to where my bike is

00:16:55.300 --> 00:16:58.300
but it looks like the big wheel will spin tonight.

00:16:58.300 --> 00:17:00.300
Translation, I got to get my bike back

00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:02.300
and the only way to do that is to get out there

00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:04.300
and kick up some dirt.

00:17:04.300 --> 00:17:14.690
More Clarissa.

00:17:14.690 --> 00:17:16.690
More Snake. After this.

00:17:16.690 --> 00:17:39.370
Help sort them, stack them and make them disappear.

00:17:39.370 --> 00:17:41.370
One player.

00:17:41.370 --> 00:17:43.370
Two players. Four, four.

00:17:43.370 --> 00:17:46.370
Yoshi's Cookie on NES and Game Boy.

00:17:46.370 --> 00:17:48.370
Cookie.

00:17:48.370 --> 00:17:51.370
From Touchstone Pictures, Michael J. Fox is a children's agent.

00:17:51.370 --> 00:17:53.370
Big deal's happening every minute.

00:17:53.370 --> 00:17:55.370
And his clients want to be actors.

00:17:55.370 --> 00:17:57.370
I want to work with Michelle Pfeiffer.

00:17:57.370 --> 00:17:59.370
In the worst way.

00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:01.370
Oh, fuck!

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:03.370
But no matter how tough it gets...

00:18:03.370 --> 00:18:05.370
How much of this slut do I have to eat today?

00:18:05.370 --> 00:18:06.370
What am I, Job?

00:18:06.370 --> 00:18:07.370
He'll never give up hope.

00:18:07.370 --> 00:18:09.370
I love that song.

00:18:09.370 --> 00:18:10.370
Me too.

00:18:10.370 --> 00:18:11.370
What were you playing?

00:18:11.370 --> 00:18:12.370
Michael J. Fox.

00:18:12.370 --> 00:18:14.370
Life with Mikey, rated PG.

00:18:14.370 --> 00:18:17.370
Starts Friday, June 4th at a theater near you.

00:18:35.100 --> 00:18:38.100
The action shouldn't catch game with the power of stretch net.

00:18:38.100 --> 00:18:41.100
That seems to squish Super Net Ball over 100 feet.

00:18:41.100 --> 00:18:44.100
Super Net Ball, yeah. Super Hot.

00:18:44.100 --> 00:18:46.100
Super Net Ball.

00:18:46.100 --> 00:18:48.100
Another great squish product from Cap Toys.

00:18:48.100 --> 00:18:49.100
Who else?

00:18:49.100 --> 00:18:51.100
Nick Mania goes loony.

00:18:51.100 --> 00:18:54.100
Bugs, Sylvester, Tweety, and that's not all, folks.

00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:57.100
Find out if you're a fud or a Bugsmeister.

00:18:57.100 --> 00:19:00.100
Watch Nick Mania tomorrow on Nick.

00:19:00.100 --> 00:19:03.100
The all new thrashers here.

00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:04.100
The Blasters.

00:19:04.100 --> 00:19:05.100
Blasher.

00:19:05.100 --> 00:19:06.100
Blast them.

00:19:06.100 --> 00:19:08.100
No one can chump me.

00:19:08.100 --> 00:19:09.100
The Blasters.

00:19:09.100 --> 00:19:10.100
Blasher is awesome.

00:19:10.100 --> 00:19:12.100
The power is complete.

00:19:12.100 --> 00:19:32.090
The other hair blasters from Tycho.

00:19:32.090 --> 00:19:36.090
The world television premiere of a Disney favorite.

00:19:36.090 --> 00:19:39.090
The adventurous tale of a parcel of precocious puppies

00:19:39.090 --> 00:19:45.090
and their perilous plight to escape the clutches of the creepy Cruella de Vil.

00:19:45.090 --> 00:19:51.010
You won't see this anywhere else.

00:19:51.010 --> 00:20:03.080
It's 101 Dalmatians premiering on the Disney Channel.

00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:05.080
Clarissa explains it all.

00:20:22.630 --> 00:20:25.630
I wanted to have my stolen bike back in time to go to the movies tonight.

00:20:25.630 --> 00:20:27.630
I was all charged up to look for it.

00:20:27.630 --> 00:20:29.630
But after spending a couple days running around,

00:20:29.630 --> 00:20:31.630
I think my batteries worn out.

00:20:31.630 --> 00:20:33.630
Here are some of the things I did.

00:20:33.630 --> 00:20:36.630
First, I put posters up all over town.

00:20:36.630 --> 00:20:37.630
Didn't get any response.

00:20:37.630 --> 00:20:38.630
It's true.

00:20:38.630 --> 00:20:40.630
Reading is a dying art.

00:20:40.630 --> 00:20:44.630
Then I went door-to-door asking if anybody'd seen any suspicious characters.

00:20:44.630 --> 00:20:46.630
Nobody had anything to say about my bike.

00:20:46.630 --> 00:20:49.630
But the whole neighborhood is talking about Mr. Babelbrook's new to pay.

00:20:49.630 --> 00:20:52.630
Turns out, he isn't fooling anyone.

00:20:52.630 --> 00:20:54.630
I even went to the used bike store to see if somebody sold it.

00:20:54.630 --> 00:20:56.630
Saw a lot of bikes.

00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:57.630
None of them were mine.

00:20:57.630 --> 00:20:59.630
The worst part is I had to walk everywhere.

00:20:59.630 --> 00:21:02.630
If only I had a bike, finding my bike would be easier.

00:21:02.630 --> 00:21:04.630
Should I really have to deal with this at my age?

00:21:04.630 --> 00:21:07.630
Am I reduced to begging for rides until I get my license?

00:21:07.630 --> 00:21:10.910
Mom, are you busy?

00:21:10.910 --> 00:21:11.910
Kind of, Clarissa. Why?

00:21:11.910 --> 00:21:13.910
Well, what about later? Are you busy later?

00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:14.910
What's on your mind?

00:21:14.910 --> 00:21:15.910
I'm looking for a ride to the multiplex.

00:21:15.910 --> 00:21:17.910
Sorry, dear. I've already run my errands.

00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:20.910
Plus, I have to finish this budget for the children's museum.

00:21:20.910 --> 00:21:21.910
I'm never going to get anywhere.

00:21:21.910 --> 00:21:23.910
Well, there is another solution, you know.

00:21:23.910 --> 00:21:24.910
You'll let me drive?

00:21:24.910 --> 00:21:27.910
No. I mean, you can borrow your brother's bike.

00:21:27.910 --> 00:21:28.910
Ugh. I'd rather walk.

00:21:28.910 --> 00:21:30.910
Well, it's up to you.

00:21:30.910 --> 00:21:33.190
Great.

00:21:33.190 --> 00:21:35.190
The perfect ending to a lousy day.

00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:37.190
Crawling to Furgwood for help.

00:21:37.190 --> 00:21:41.190
Well, I guess you got to crawl before you can ride.

00:21:41.190 --> 00:21:49.040
Who is it?

00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:52.420
Can I talk to you a minute, Ferguson?

00:21:52.420 --> 00:21:54.420
Ferguson?

00:21:54.420 --> 00:21:58.420
Ferguson, not Furgwad, Furgturd, or Furgbreath?

00:21:58.420 --> 00:22:00.420
Somebody must want something.

00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:01.420
Enter.

00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:05.810
I need a favor.

00:22:05.810 --> 00:22:08.810
Well, I'm a reasonable man. Ask away.

00:22:08.810 --> 00:22:10.810
I need your bike just for tonight.

00:22:10.810 --> 00:22:13.810
My bike? You want to borrow my bike?

00:22:13.810 --> 00:22:14.810
Do you have to rub it in?

00:22:14.810 --> 00:22:17.810
Have to? Nah, I choose to.

00:22:17.810 --> 00:22:21.810
Besides, this is from the woman who begrudged me not only a computer,

00:22:21.810 --> 00:22:23.810
but a ruler as well.

00:22:23.810 --> 00:22:26.810
At least I'm asking first, and believe me, it's painful.

00:22:26.810 --> 00:22:28.810
Oh, let's dwell on that a moment.

00:22:28.810 --> 00:22:30.810
Okay, you can use my computer.

00:22:30.810 --> 00:22:32.810
Nope. Too little, too late, too bad.

00:22:32.810 --> 00:22:34.810
Besides, I handed in that report days ago.

00:22:34.810 --> 00:22:36.810
Come on, Ferguson, just lend it to me.

00:22:36.810 --> 00:22:39.810
No, sis, because while I understand your needs,

00:22:39.810 --> 00:22:41.810
somebody's got to look out for mine.

00:22:41.810 --> 00:22:42.810
What are you talking about?

00:22:42.810 --> 00:22:47.810
Well, suppose, just suppose I lent you my bike.

00:22:47.810 --> 00:22:48.810
Would that be prudent?

00:22:48.810 --> 00:22:51.810
We have clear evidence that a bike is not safe in your hands.

00:22:51.810 --> 00:22:53.810
I'll lock it up.

00:22:53.810 --> 00:22:55.810
Oh, and then there's the wear and tear in the tires.

00:22:55.810 --> 00:22:57.810
I'll give you a dollar.

00:23:00.810 --> 00:23:03.810
You're on. Come with me.

00:23:03.810 --> 00:23:08.780
Wait, you must be joking.

00:23:08.780 --> 00:23:11.780
This is your crummy old bike that Clifford wrapped around a tree.

00:23:11.780 --> 00:23:14.780
You never specified making model. Happy riding.

00:23:14.780 --> 00:23:17.780
Forget it. Give me the rock band of $4,000 or my dollar back.

00:23:17.780 --> 00:23:19.780
Sorry, sis. I can't make that deal.

00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:23.780
I'll tell you what. You take this one off my hands for $10 even.

00:23:23.780 --> 00:23:25.780
With a little work, it could be a real beaut.

00:23:25.780 --> 00:23:26.780
I can't believe this.

00:23:26.780 --> 00:23:27.780
Take it or leave it?

00:23:27.780 --> 00:23:29.780
Let me see if I've got it.

00:23:29.780 --> 00:23:36.900
Here's a one, a five, and four more ones.

00:23:36.900 --> 00:23:38.900
Thank you. Thank you.

00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:41.900
I think I'll add this to my presidential portrait collection.

00:23:41.900 --> 00:23:43.900
Goodbye, my dear old bike.

00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:45.900
Take good care of it, sis.

00:23:45.900 --> 00:23:48.900
I've got a lot of fond memories of my riding days with this bike.

00:23:48.900 --> 00:23:50.900
If these folks could talk,

00:23:50.900 --> 00:23:51.900
they'd say...

00:23:51.900 --> 00:23:53.900
Shut up.

00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:54.900
Okay.

00:23:57.360 --> 00:23:58.360
Great.

00:23:58.360 --> 00:24:01.360
Here I am ready for a four-in-the-floor convertible,

00:24:01.360 --> 00:24:05.360
and I'm forced to ride my little brother's two-wheel leftovers.

00:24:05.360 --> 00:24:08.360
Well, I may have outgrown a bike, but it looks like I still need a bike.

00:24:08.360 --> 00:24:11.360
I may have stuck with this thing, or I'm stuck at home.

00:24:11.360 --> 00:24:15.820
Okay.

00:24:15.820 --> 00:24:20.820
You put on new brake pads, new wheels, new fork,

00:24:20.820 --> 00:24:23.820
straighten out the handlebars, and attach to new fender.

00:24:23.820 --> 00:24:25.820
So when you think about it, for $10?

00:24:25.820 --> 00:24:28.820
$10? After what I spent on parts?

00:24:28.820 --> 00:24:29.820
You saved on labor.

00:24:29.820 --> 00:24:32.820
Yeah, thanks, Sam. You're real whiz with a wrench.

00:24:32.820 --> 00:24:34.820
Hey, we worked together.

00:24:34.820 --> 00:24:37.820
And I've got to say, we really got it to look like...

