01:32:12.070 --> 01:32:14.070
All the little kids are always like,

01:32:14.070 --> 01:32:15.070
ooh.

01:32:16.070 --> 01:32:18.070
There's no place like home.

01:32:19.070 --> 01:32:20.070
And then blackout.

01:32:50.040 --> 01:32:52.040
We feel an accessory set sold separately.

01:32:55.280 --> 01:32:56.280
Wrong, Brontosaurus breath.

01:32:56.280 --> 01:32:57.280
I'm not just a dinosaur.

01:32:57.280 --> 01:32:58.280
I'm Rocky D.

01:32:58.280 --> 01:33:00.280
Dinosaur extraordinaire.

01:33:01.280 --> 01:33:02.280
Wow, you eat rocks?

01:33:02.280 --> 01:33:03.280
Well, certainly not those hard things

01:33:03.280 --> 01:33:04.280
you find on the ground,

01:33:04.280 --> 01:33:06.280
but these totally cool,

01:33:06.280 --> 01:33:07.280
new, soft and chewy

01:33:07.280 --> 01:33:08.280
Brox rox candies.

01:33:08.280 --> 01:33:09.280
Look like rocks.

01:33:09.280 --> 01:33:10.280
Feel like rocks.

01:33:10.280 --> 01:33:12.280
Hey, they don't taste like rocks.

01:33:12.280 --> 01:33:13.280
They're green.

01:33:13.280 --> 01:33:15.280
Yup, five dynamite fruit flavors.

01:33:15.280 --> 01:33:16.280
Excellent.

01:33:16.280 --> 01:33:17.280
You can get your rocks

01:33:17.280 --> 01:33:18.280
from Brox.

01:33:18.280 --> 01:33:19.280
Brox rox.

01:33:19.280 --> 01:33:20.280
Now, we're rockin'

01:33:20.280 --> 01:33:22.280
with Brox rox.

01:33:23.280 --> 01:33:24.280
Hey, Squirt.

01:33:24.280 --> 01:33:25.280
Meet Lisa.

01:33:25.280 --> 01:33:26.280
I invited her for breakfast.

01:33:26.280 --> 01:33:27.280
Nice.

01:33:27.280 --> 01:33:28.280
Can I have another bowl, Billy?

01:33:28.280 --> 01:33:29.280
Sure.

01:33:29.280 --> 01:33:31.280
She's got my Kellogg's Corn Pops.

01:33:31.280 --> 01:33:32.280
Stay calm.

01:33:32.280 --> 01:33:33.280
Sorry.

01:33:33.280 --> 01:33:34.280
Sorry.

01:33:34.280 --> 01:33:35.280
You ate all my pops.

01:33:35.280 --> 01:33:36.280
Oh, what that tastes like,

01:33:36.280 --> 01:33:37.280
sweet popcorn.

01:33:37.280 --> 01:33:38.280
And all you can say

01:33:38.280 --> 01:33:39.280
is Miss Space Canette

01:33:39.280 --> 01:33:40.280
with my loser brother

01:33:40.280 --> 01:33:41.280
for her boyfriend is sorry.

01:33:41.280 --> 01:33:42.280
What am I going to do?

01:33:42.280 --> 01:33:43.280
Billy, didn't you have

01:33:43.280 --> 01:33:45.280
Megan over for Corn Pops last week?

01:33:45.280 --> 01:33:46.280
Megan Keller.

01:33:46.280 --> 01:33:47.280
I'm not hungry.

01:33:47.280 --> 01:33:48.280
Aw.

01:33:48.280 --> 01:33:49.280
Kellogg's Corn Pops

01:33:49.280 --> 01:33:51.280
is part of this complete breakfast.

01:33:51.280 --> 01:33:53.280
I gotta have my pops.

01:33:53.280 --> 01:33:55.280
This is the Super Soaker 50,

01:33:55.280 --> 01:33:57.280
the air-powered water gun

01:33:57.280 --> 01:33:58.280
that shoots so far

01:33:58.280 --> 01:34:00.280
that while you can run,

01:34:00.280 --> 01:34:02.280
you can't hide.

01:34:03.280 --> 01:34:05.280
The genuine Super Soaker 50.

01:34:05.280 --> 01:34:06.280
If you don't have one,

01:34:06.280 --> 01:34:08.280
you're all wet.

01:34:19.280 --> 01:34:55.970
What was that?

01:34:55.970 --> 01:34:57.970
What?

01:34:57.970 --> 01:34:58.970
I thought I heard something,

01:34:58.970 --> 01:35:00.970
like an animal or something.

01:35:00.970 --> 01:35:09.690
Nobody here but us chickens.

01:35:09.690 --> 01:35:11.690
Very funny.

01:35:11.690 --> 01:35:12.690
You let me do it.

01:35:12.690 --> 01:35:13.690
I can do it.

01:35:13.690 --> 01:35:15.690
Give me the matches.

01:35:15.690 --> 01:35:17.690
Where's Kristen?

01:35:17.690 --> 01:35:18.690
She'll be here to get

01:35:18.690 --> 01:35:19.690
your shorts in a knot.

01:35:19.690 --> 01:35:20.690
Yeah.

01:35:20.690 --> 01:35:21.690
After the work is all done,

01:35:21.690 --> 01:35:22.690
she wouldn't want to

01:35:22.690 --> 01:35:23.690
break her fingernails.

01:35:23.690 --> 01:35:26.190
Ouch.

01:35:26.190 --> 01:35:27.190
I'm going to have to

01:35:27.190 --> 01:35:29.190
make a rule about latecomers.

01:35:29.190 --> 01:35:33.050
What was that?

01:35:33.050 --> 01:35:35.050
Sounded like a hound dog.

01:35:35.050 --> 01:35:37.050
Maybe it was Kristen.

01:35:37.050 --> 01:35:39.050
She's no dog.

01:35:39.050 --> 01:35:55.950
Hey, guys.

01:35:55.950 --> 01:35:56.950
I had to pick up Elvis.

01:35:56.950 --> 01:35:58.950
And who's Elvis?

01:35:58.950 --> 01:35:59.950
Dean.

01:35:59.950 --> 01:36:00.950
But a hound dog.

01:36:00.950 --> 01:36:02.950
My dad says Elvis is king.

01:36:02.950 --> 01:36:03.950
So, Kristen,

01:36:03.950 --> 01:36:04.950
are you going to tell us a story?

01:36:04.950 --> 01:36:05.950
You're just going to sit there

01:36:05.950 --> 01:36:07.950
scaring us with Elvis.

01:36:07.950 --> 01:36:08.950
I have a tail

01:36:08.950 --> 01:36:09.950
that'll have you

01:36:09.950 --> 01:36:11.950
shaking in your little mouth.

01:36:14.950 --> 01:36:17.950
Elvis is here for the sound effects.

01:36:17.950 --> 01:36:21.780
I need some help with the dust, Dave.

01:36:21.780 --> 01:36:23.780
Submitted for the approval

01:36:23.780 --> 01:36:25.780
of the Midnight Society.

01:36:25.780 --> 01:36:27.780
I call this story

01:36:27.780 --> 01:36:34.580
the tale of the hungry hounds.

01:36:34.580 --> 01:36:45.930
Many days, Pam liked to rummage

01:36:45.930 --> 01:36:47.930
around in her musty old attic.

01:36:47.930 --> 01:36:50.530
Her mother never threw

01:36:50.530 --> 01:36:55.470
anything away.

01:36:55.470 --> 01:36:56.470
There was stuff from Pam's

01:36:56.470 --> 01:36:57.470
grandparents,

01:36:57.470 --> 01:36:59.470
from relatives,

01:36:59.470 --> 01:37:00.470
and ancestors who'd been

01:37:00.470 --> 01:37:02.470
dead for years.

01:37:02.470 --> 01:37:03.470
One summer,

01:37:03.470 --> 01:37:04.470
Pam's cousin Amy

01:37:04.470 --> 01:37:06.470
was visiting from the city.

01:37:12.460 --> 01:37:13.460
Come here.

01:37:13.460 --> 01:37:14.460
Look at this.

01:37:14.460 --> 01:37:16.460
Isn't this great?

01:37:16.460 --> 01:37:17.460
Grandpa wore this on

01:37:17.460 --> 01:37:19.460
at his wedding.

01:37:19.460 --> 01:37:20.460
Just think,

01:37:20.460 --> 01:37:21.460
my mother

01:37:21.460 --> 01:37:22.460
and your father

01:37:22.460 --> 01:37:25.460
were just a twinkle in his eye.

01:37:25.460 --> 01:37:26.460
But I guess

01:37:26.460 --> 01:37:28.460
Aunt Dora came first.

01:37:28.460 --> 01:37:31.000
Amy,

01:37:31.000 --> 01:37:36.770
look at this.

01:37:36.770 --> 01:38:00.080
Nearly time for the wedding.

01:38:00.080 --> 01:38:02.080
This isn't funny.

01:38:02.080 --> 01:38:06.060
Oh, give me a break.

01:38:06.060 --> 01:38:07.060
You don't really believe

01:38:07.060 --> 01:38:08.060
in ghosts, do you?

01:38:08.060 --> 01:38:09.060
There are more things

01:38:09.060 --> 01:38:10.060
on heaven and earth

01:38:10.060 --> 01:38:12.060
that you could ever dream of,

01:38:12.060 --> 01:38:13.060
says Hugh.

01:38:13.060 --> 01:38:14.060
Hamlet,

01:38:14.060 --> 01:38:15.060
his father's ghost

01:38:15.060 --> 01:38:16.060
made him do things

01:38:16.060 --> 01:38:17.060
that he didn't want to do.

01:38:17.060 --> 01:38:18.060
Like what?

01:38:18.060 --> 01:38:19.060
Like kill his uncle

01:38:19.060 --> 01:38:20.060
for marrying his mother.

01:38:20.060 --> 01:38:21.060
Nice.

01:38:21.060 --> 01:38:23.060
Glad we're not in that family.

01:38:23.060 --> 01:38:26.060
I don't believe in ghosts anyways.

01:38:26.060 --> 01:38:43.070
I didn't know you could ride.

01:38:43.070 --> 01:38:45.070
I can't.

01:38:45.070 --> 01:38:47.070
Mom won't let me.

01:38:47.070 --> 01:38:48.070
This is Aunt Dora,

01:38:48.070 --> 01:38:50.070
and that's her horse mirage.

01:38:50.070 --> 01:38:53.070
She sure looked like you.

01:38:53.070 --> 01:38:54.070
Let's go.

01:38:54.070 --> 01:38:56.070
I don't know.

01:38:56.070 --> 01:38:58.070
It's coming from in there.

01:38:58.070 --> 01:39:12.870
Come on, help me.

01:39:12.870 --> 01:39:14.870
Look, there's a name.

01:39:14.870 --> 01:39:16.870
Dora Peace.

01:39:16.870 --> 01:39:20.870
1963.

01:39:20.870 --> 01:39:22.870
Come on, this is too creepy.

01:39:22.870 --> 01:39:29.160
It's probably just a mouse.

01:39:29.160 --> 01:39:30.160
We shouldn't touch it.

01:39:30.160 --> 01:39:33.160
Mom says let the dead rest in peace.

01:39:33.160 --> 01:39:38.160
Look, there's a little mouse hole.

01:39:38.160 --> 01:39:41.880
It's a combination

01:39:41.880 --> 01:39:42.880
and we'll let you free.

01:39:42.880 --> 01:39:43.880
Come on, Amy.

01:39:43.880 --> 01:39:44.880
Come on down.

01:39:44.880 --> 01:39:46.880
Now it's time to feed the dog.

01:39:46.880 --> 01:39:47.880
Let's go.

01:39:47.880 --> 01:40:03.360
I can't believe that I have to spend

01:40:03.360 --> 01:40:05.360
my entire summer here.

01:40:05.360 --> 01:40:08.360
What do you do for fun anyways?

01:40:08.360 --> 01:40:10.360
Promise you won't tell?

01:40:10.360 --> 01:40:12.360
Let's go.

01:40:12.360 --> 01:40:20.080
His owners live in the city.

01:40:20.080 --> 01:40:21.080
They only come here

01:40:21.080 --> 01:40:22.080
on weekends though.

01:40:22.080 --> 01:40:23.080
Does it bite?

01:40:23.080 --> 01:40:25.080
Nah, he's just a big baby.

01:40:25.080 --> 01:40:31.140
Watch.

01:40:31.140 --> 01:40:32.140
Good boy.

01:40:32.140 --> 01:40:34.140
So he's like a big dog.

01:40:34.140 --> 01:40:35.140
So what?

01:40:35.140 --> 01:40:36.140
Watch this.

01:40:36.140 --> 01:40:45.810
Ma'am!

01:40:45.810 --> 01:40:47.810
Are you alright?

01:40:47.810 --> 01:40:52.080
The animals are dangerous.

01:40:52.080 --> 01:40:54.080
I told you never to go near them.

01:40:54.080 --> 01:40:55.080
It wouldn't be dangerous

01:40:55.080 --> 01:40:57.080
if I knew how to ride.

01:40:57.080 --> 01:40:59.080
Can I just take some lessons?

01:40:59.080 --> 01:41:00.080
No.

01:41:00.080 --> 01:41:01.080
And I wish you wouldn't bring

01:41:01.080 --> 01:41:03.080
this up to top again.

01:41:03.080 --> 01:41:04.080
It's dinner time.

01:41:04.080 --> 01:41:05.080
Let's go home.

01:41:05.080 --> 01:41:07.080
But it's safe in a ring.

01:41:07.080 --> 01:41:09.080
I don't want to discuss it.

01:41:09.080 --> 01:41:11.080
Mom, it happened 30 years ago.

01:41:11.080 --> 01:41:14.080
Seems like yesterday to me.

01:41:14.080 --> 01:41:17.740
You better give it a rest.

01:41:17.740 --> 01:41:35.140
We'll work with just one person.

01:41:35.140 --> 01:41:37.140
This is feeble.

01:41:37.140 --> 01:41:39.140
Don't you do anything around here

01:41:39.140 --> 01:41:41.140
except play games?

01:41:41.140 --> 01:41:42.140
What are we going to do next,

01:41:42.140 --> 01:41:43.140
Jethro?

01:41:43.140 --> 01:41:44.140
Shuck some corn?

01:41:44.140 --> 01:41:45.140
Come on.

01:41:45.140 --> 01:41:46.140
Humor me.

01:41:46.140 --> 01:41:50.000
I found it in the attic.

01:41:50.000 --> 01:41:51.000
The spirits were supposed to

01:41:51.000 --> 01:41:53.000
give us messages from the other world.

01:41:53.000 --> 01:41:54.000
Maybe they can tell us

01:41:54.000 --> 01:41:55.000
where to get a pizza.

01:41:55.000 --> 01:41:56.000
Amy.

01:41:56.000 --> 01:41:58.000
I'm sorry.

01:41:58.000 --> 01:42:00.000
Let's visit the far side.

01:42:00.000 --> 01:42:01.000
Mom said that she and Aunt Dora

01:42:01.000 --> 01:42:03.000
used to do this when they were kids.

01:42:04.000 --> 01:42:09.260
Doing this, right?

01:42:09.260 --> 01:42:35.770
It's spelled let me out.

01:42:35.770 --> 01:42:37.770
Let me out.

01:42:37.770 --> 01:42:39.770
Maybe it's that rodent calling

01:42:39.770 --> 01:42:41.770
from Aunt Dora's box.

01:42:44.770 --> 01:42:45.770
One.

01:42:46.770 --> 01:42:47.770
Four.

01:42:47.770 --> 01:42:58.120
What if it works?

01:42:58.120 --> 01:42:59.120
We're just going to open it up

01:42:59.120 --> 01:43:00.120
and take a look.

01:43:00.120 --> 01:43:01.120
What's the big deal?

01:43:01.120 --> 01:43:02.120
Yeah, but you saw how upset

01:43:02.120 --> 01:43:04.120
my mom got it.

01:43:04.120 --> 01:43:05.120
It's like she's haunted by

01:43:05.120 --> 01:43:06.120
her sister.

01:43:06.120 --> 01:43:08.120
If she catches it...

01:43:09.120 --> 01:43:10.120
Look.

01:43:10.120 --> 01:43:12.120
It can fit through that mouse hole.

01:43:12.120 --> 01:43:14.120
It's not big enough to hurt us.

01:43:14.120 --> 01:43:16.120
Yeah, but what if it's something else?

01:43:16.120 --> 01:43:18.120
Like what?

01:43:18.120 --> 01:43:19.120
Now what were those numbers?

01:43:19.120 --> 01:43:20.120
One, four, nine.

01:43:20.120 --> 01:43:21.120
Look, I'm telling you,

